Structures

struct point {
  int x;
  int y;
};

a structure declares a type

e.g. struct { ... } x, y, z;

declares 3 vars of the type of struct, just like int x, y, z;

struct point pt;

defines a structure pt of type point

struct pt maxpt = { 320, 200 };

how do we access structs?

structure-name.member

e.g. printf("%d,%d", pt.x, pt.y);

nested structures:

struct rect {
  struct point pt1;
  struct point pt2;
}
